  <h2>Interests</h2>
  <p>
    I am passionate about front-end development, even though it's not my current
    job, it is definitely my interest. I enjoy exploring how to create both
    visually appealing and powerful user interfaces through code. In my free
    time, I self-learn front-end knowledge, hoping to make it my profession in
    the future.
  </p>
  <p>
    When I'm not coding, I like reading books, watching movies, or looking for
    niche games to pass the time. Reading allows me to explore different
    perspectives and ideas, which often inspire innovative solutions in my
    coding projects. Movies, with their visual storytelling, help me understand
    the importance of narrative and engagement in user experience design. And
    games, with their interactivity and immersion, spark my curiosity about what
    makes digital experiences truly captivating.
  </p>
